{"lemma":"غَداة","slug":"غَداة","root":"غ.د.#","root_slug":"غ-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَداة","root":"غدو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31537"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"daybreak, dawn, early morning","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: عَشِيِّ (ʕašiyyi)"},{"text":"سَلُوا قَلْبِي غَدَاةَ سَلَا وَثَابَا\n لَعَلَّ عَلَى ٱلْجَمَالِ لَهُ عِتَابًا\n وَيُسْأَلُ فِي ٱلْحَوَادِثِ ذُو صَوَابٍ\n فَهَلْ تَرَكَ ٱلْجَمَالُ لَهُ صَوَابًا","english":"Ask my heart the early morning it forgets and returns to its previous state\n Perhaps towards the beautiful one it has some reproach\n Only wise people are supposed to be asked\n Did the beauty leave any wisdom to it"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣa.daːh/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31537","headword_ar":"غَدَاةٌ","root":"gdw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places: though [properly] fem., and not heard as made mase., it may be made mase. if meant to be understood as signifying the “ first part of the day: ” (IAmb, Msb:) it is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadawapN","text_ar":"غَدَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadawaAtN","text_ar":"غَدَوَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IHsh, TA.) One says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=tiyka gadaApa gadK","text_ar":"ا=تِيكَ غَدَاةَ غَدٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will come to thee in the early part of the morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of to-morrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@logadaApi waA@loEa$iY~i","text_ar":"بِا@لْغَدَاةِ وَا@لْعَشِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur [vi. 52 and xviii. 27] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"After the prayer of daybreak and"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayer of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the period of the afternoon called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSor","text_ar":"عَصْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to some, [it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning and the evening,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the forenoon and the afternoon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for they say that] it denotes constancy of religious service: Ibn-'Ámir and Aboo-'Abd-erRahmán Es-Sulamee read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loEa$iY~i","text_ar":"وَا@لْعَشِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@logudowapi","text_ar":"بِا@لْغُدْوَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the former is the common reading; and A 'Obeyd says, we think that they read thus following the handwriting, for it is written in all the copies of the Kur-án with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alawp","text_ar":"الصَّلَوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~akawp","text_ar":"الزَّكَوة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and this is not an indication of the reading [which they have adopted], as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlSlwp","text_ar":"الصلوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alzkwp","text_ar":"الزكوة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not pronounced [otherwise than as an] of prolongation except that it requires the fet-hah that follows to be uttered with a somewhat broad sound]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A@bonu gadaAtayoni","text_ar":"هُوَ ا@بْنُ غَدَاتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is a son of two days"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is two days old"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  The dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guday~apN","text_ar":"غُدَيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or this is the dim. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gudowapN","text_ar":"غُدْوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (EM p. 56:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arokabu","text_ar":"اَرْكَبُ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2235},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilayohi guday~apF","text_ar":"اـِلَيْهِ غُدَيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will ride to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in a short period of an early part of a morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: and one says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*atayotuhu guday~aAnaAtK","text_ar":"ذَتَيْتُهُ غُدَيَّانَاتٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in short periods of early parts of mornings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; an anomalous [pl.] dim. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$ay~aAnaAt","text_ar":"عُشَيَّانَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"; both of which are mentioned by Sb. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["IAmb","Msb","TA"]}]}}